This paper is likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category as it focuses on the training of capsule networks, which are a type of neural network. Additionally, the paper proposes a new routing algorithm to improve the training of these networks, which is a common topic in the field of neural computing.

The paper also involves computer vision tasks, such as object recognition, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.

The use of machine learning techniques to train the capsule networks makes it likely that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.

The paper's focus on improving the robustness of the network to adversarial attacks suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category, which often deals with issues of security and safety in AI systems.

Finally, the paper's use of natural language processing techniques to describe the capsule network architecture and routing algorithm suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
